abstract: Papua New Guinea officials say police fired on student protesters in capital of Port Moresby, and over 20 people were wounded; protesters are calling for Prime Min Peter O'Neill to resign in connection with long-running corruption scandal.
lead_paragraph: Officials said some demonstrators had been wounded, but none killed. Students have been demanding that Prime Minister Peter O’Neill resign.

headline.main: Papua New Guinea Protesters Wounded by Police Gunfire, Lawmaker Says
headline.print_headline: Over 20 Hurt as Police Fire on Protesters
